WEBVTT

1
00:01:57.368 --> 00:01:58.767
That one.

2
00:02:03.249 --> 00:02:04.647
Here, boy.

3
00:02:08.528 --> 00:02:10.008
You're heavy.

4
00:02:12.728 --> 00:02:14.247
And slobbery.

5
00:02:20.408 --> 00:02:21.647
There.

6
00:02:22.449 --> 00:02:24.207
You're a good boy.

7
00:02:26.009 --> 00:02:27.727
You're my good boy.

8
00:02:35.249 --> 00:02:36.488
Hello?

9
00:02:38.448 --> 00:02:40.808
Penny,
I don't have much time.

10
00:02:40.889 --> 00:02:43.568
Daddy?
Are you okay?

11
00:02:44.328 --> 00:02:47.208
Something's come
up at work, honey.

12
00:02:47.288 --> 00:02:49.807
Daddy's not gonna be
home for a while.

13
00:02:51.289 --> 00:02:52.807
I don't understand.

14
00:02:52.889 --> 00:02:55.688
You can't go back
to the house, Penny. Okay?

15
00:02:56.888 --> 00:02:58.488
What's happening?

16
00:02:59.329 --> 00:03:03.128
It's all right. You
won't be alone. You have Bolt.

17
00:03:04.888 --> 00:03:06.487
I've altered him.

18
00:03:23.449 --> 00:03:30.048
He can protect you now.

19
00:03:44.888 --> 00:03:50.888
The doctor has been taken care of,
which, of course, is wonderful news.

20
00:03:50.969 --> 00:03:53.807
Everything is
positioning nicely.

21
00:03:54.288 --> 00:03:57.367
There he is. Dr Calico.

22
00:03:59.688 --> 00:04:02.567
Any luck getting our
guest to spill his guts?

23
00:04:02.649 --> 00:04:08.248
Oh! His guts will spill,
one way or another.

24
00:04:08.328 --> 00:04:10.168
Never! I'll never talk.

25
00:04:11.689 --> 00:04:13.287
Daddy!

26
00:04:13.369 --> 00:04:18.647
You're beginning to irk me, Professor.
I am irked, and that will not do.

27
00:04:19.208 --> 00:04:21.128
Has the package arrived?

28
00:04:21.209 --> 00:04:26.328
I think it might make our dear
friend a bit more communicative.

29
00:04:26.409 --> 00:04:28.568
I'm sending an agent
to pick it up.

30
00:04:28.689 --> 00:04:33.368
Gorgeous! Have him bring it
to me on the first flight.

31
00:04:47.569 --> 00:04:49.047
Bolt, let's go.

32
00:05:14.168 --> 00:05:16.488
We only need the girl.

33
00:05:49.169 --> 00:05:50.247
What?

34
00:05:50.329 --> 00:05:53.448
- Where's Calico?
- I'm not talking to you.

35
00:05:55.129 --> 00:05:58.488
Bolivia! Bolivia!
Calico's in Bolivia!

36
00:05:58.609 --> 00:06:00.408
Near Lake Rogaguado!

37
00:06:01.609 --> 00:06:04.008
Lake Rogaguado! I
should've known.

38
00:06:10.408 --> 00:06:12.968
- Come on, Bolt. Let's go!
- No!

39
00:06:36.089 --> 00:06:39.288
Bolivia. There's a flight
leaving in 10 minutes.

40
00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:53.528
Bolt! Zoom, zoom.

41
00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:45.608
Bolt, fetch.

42
00:08:02.969 --> 00:08:04.088
Puppy!

43
00:09:22.010 --> 00:09:23.049
Good boy.

44
00:09:24.209 --> 00:09:25.368
Airport.

45
00:09:27.930 --> 00:09:29.049
Uh-oh!

46
00:09:34.089 --> 00:09:35.889
Bolt, speak.

47
00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:16.889
Okay, okay. Good job, buddy.

48
00:10:18.649 --> 00:10:20.408
Mission accomplished.

49
00:10:23.129 --> 00:10:24.489
That's a keeper.

50
00:10:25.809 --> 00:10:28.569
It's all right, tough guy.
You got them all.

51
00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:35.449
Don't worry, Bolt. You
saved the day again.

52
00:10:38.809 --> 00:10:40.728
All right. Good job.
Let's strike the set.

53
00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:46.249
We're gonna need a cable guard
on set for that move tomorrow.

54
00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:47.889
Yeah. All right.

55
00:10:51.130 --> 00:10:52.169
Good boy.

56
00:10:53.329 --> 00:10:54.489
Airport.

57
00:10:57.170 --> 00:10:58.329
Uh-oh!

58
00:11:02.170 --> 00:11:03.929
Bolt, speak.

59
00:11:07.090 --> 00:11:08.489
- Boom Mike.
- We got a boom Mike.

60
00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:10.168
It's a boom Mike.

61
00:11:11.770 --> 00:11:13.529
That's sloppy.

62
00:11:13.609 --> 00:11:17.209
The dog could've seen that.
He could've seen that.

63
00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:20.569
Uh... Who cares if
the dog sees a boom Mike?

64
00:11:21.009 --> 00:11:22.809
What? Who's that?

65
00:11:22.890 --> 00:11:26.369
Forgive me for answering a
question with a question,

66
00:11:26.690 --> 00:11:29.449
but who are you?

67
00:11:29.850 --> 00:11:33.169
- Mindy Parker, from the network.
- Of course.

68
00:11:34.010 --> 00:11:37.209
Let me ask you, Mindy
from the network,

69
00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:39.128
what do you see here?

70
00:11:39.570 --> 00:11:40.648
Uh...

71
00:11:40.889 --> 00:11:43.729
- The dog.
- "The dog," she says.

72
00:11:44.489 --> 00:11:48.729
Oh, Mindy. Poor, poor, Mindy.

73
00:11:49.129 --> 00:11:51.290
Am I missing something?

74
00:11:51.411 --> 00:11:54.089
You're missing
everything, Mindy.

75
00:11:54.170 --> 00:11:56.008
You see a dog.

76
00:11:56.090 --> 00:12:02.089
I see an animal who believes with every
fibre of his being, every fibre,

77
00:12:02.170 --> 00:12:04.729
that the girl he loves
is in mortal danger.

78
00:12:04.850 --> 00:12:06.809
I see a depth of emotion
on the face of that canine

79
00:12:06.890 --> 00:12:10.968
the likes of which has never
been captured on screen before!

80
00:12:11.089 --> 00:12:13.689
Never, Mindy from the network!

81
00:12:13.690 --> 00:12:14.648
Hmm.

82
00:12:14.769 --> 00:12:19.609
We jump through hoops to make sure
that Bolt believes everything is real.

83
00:12:19.690 --> 00:12:22.889
It's why we don't miss marks.
It's why we don't reshoot,

84
00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:27.770
and it's why we most certainly do
not let the dog see boom Mikes!

85
00:12:29.930 --> 00:12:33.049
Because, Mindy from the network,

86
00:12:34.330 --> 00:12:40.848
if the dog believes it,
the audience believes it.

87
00:12:42.731 --> 00:12:44.729
Wow. Okay.

88
00:12:44.850 --> 00:12:48.729
You want reality? Here you go, chief.
The show's too predictable.

89
00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:52.089
The girl's in danger, the dog saves her
from the creepy English guy, we get it.

90
00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:53.449
There's always a happy ending.

91
00:12:53.530 --> 00:12:56.810
And our focus groups tell us
18-to-35-year-olds are unhappy.

92
00:12:56.890 --> 00:12:58.489
They're not happy with happy.

93
00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:00.409
So maybe you should,
I don't know,

94
00:13:00.490 --> 00:13:03.129
spend a little less time worrying
about the dog's Method acting

95
00:13:03.210 --> 00:13:04.249
and more time figuring out

96
00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:06.730
how to stop 20-year-olds in
Topeka from changing the channel.

97
00:13:06.810 --> 00:13:09.529
Because if you lose so much
as half a rating point,

98
00:13:09.610 --> 00:13:13.689
so help me, I will fire everyone
in this room, starting with you.

99
00:13:14.570 --> 00:13:16.249
How's that for real?

100
00:13:19.290 --> 00:13:21.288
There. Perfect.

101
00:13:23.451 --> 00:13:24.729
You saved me again, Bolt.

102
00:13:26.971 --> 00:13:30.809
It's okay. It's nothing.
No more bad guys.

103
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:34.329
Do you want some food, Bolty?
Are you hungry?

104
00:13:39.610 --> 00:13:42.330
You got them, Bolt. No
one's gonna hurt me.

105
00:13:44.210 --> 00:13:46.490
Bolt, look at me. I'm fine, see?

106
00:13:48.570 --> 00:13:50.649
Come here, buddy. Come here.

107
00:13:52.091 --> 00:13:54.170
Go get it, Bolt. Go get it.

108
00:13:55.849 --> 00:13:58.010
Yeah, that one's no fun either.

109
00:13:59.410 --> 00:14:01.369
Well, what do we have here?

110
00:14:01.490 --> 00:14:05.369
Your old buddy, Mr. Carrot.

111
00:14:24.090 --> 00:14:27.730
Bolt. You know I have to go.

112
00:14:42.451 --> 00:14:44.370
Yeah, you're my good boy.

113
00:14:52.251 --> 00:14:55.049
There she is. My
little superstar.

114
00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:57.210
Let's get to that Teen
Vogue cover shoot.

115
00:14:57.331 --> 00:15:00.249
Mom, I wanna take Bolt
home this weekend.

116
00:15:00.370 --> 00:15:01.690
Well, I...

117
00:15:02.131 --> 00:15:03.609
- That would be...
- That'd be nice. That'd be great.

118
00:15:03.691 --> 00:15:08.330
That would. A little girl and her dog.
Nothing better than that.

119
00:15:10.610 --> 00:15:13.649
So I can bring Bolt home?

120
00:15:13.851 --> 00:15:17.330
As your friend I say,
"Yes, absolutely,"

121
00:15:17.691 --> 00:15:21.930
but as your agent, I have to
remind you this is Bolt's world.

122
00:15:22.011 --> 00:15:25.449
He has to stay right here.
Okay, let's go.

123
00:15:25.530 --> 00:15:27.609
But he never gets
to be a real dog,

124
00:15:27.691 --> 00:15:29.610
and it would only be for the
weekend, and I just want...

125
00:15:29.690 --> 00:15:32.170
Well, you know what?
It's a fair question.

126
00:15:32.250 --> 00:15:35.370
Let's do this, let's put a pin in it.
Boop! Pin in.

127
00:15:35.450 --> 00:15:37.530
There you go. Now, let's
let that hang there a bit,

128
00:15:37.610 --> 00:15:39.529
and then we'll address that when
we've thought things through.

129
00:15:39.611 --> 00:15:41.129
Okay? Good enough for everybody?

130
00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:43.210
Smiles all around? Let's
get out of here. Come on.

131
00:15:43.291 --> 00:15:46.649
I don't need to think it through.
I wanna take Bolt home.

132
00:15:46.771 --> 00:15:49.289
Look at this face.

133
00:15:49.371 --> 00:15:51.689
I have a little girl at
home, love of my life.

134
00:15:51.771 --> 00:15:54.010
I would do anything for her,

135
00:15:54.090 --> 00:15:56.890
and I would trade her
for you in a heartbeat.

136
00:15:57.691 --> 00:15:58.970
True story.

137
00:15:59.050 --> 00:16:01.529
That reminds me, we need to
be getting over to wardrobe.

138
00:16:01.650 --> 00:16:02.810
- Clip-clip, let's go.
- But...

139
00:16:02.811 --> 00:16:04.809
- I need her in hair.
- I just...

140
00:16:04.890 --> 00:16:06.489
Can I get her for
five minutes in makeup?

141
00:16:06.570 --> 00:16:09.210
I wanna go for something
more natural.

142
00:16:13.850 --> 00:16:17.210
So the dog
thinks this is all real?

143
00:16:17.331 --> 00:16:18.970
Oh, yeah, you're new.

144
00:16:19.091 --> 00:16:21.610
Guy never leaves the set.
It's unbelievable.

145
00:16:21.690 --> 00:16:25.369
Whenever I get the chance, this
is the perfect way to unwind.

146
00:16:27.211 --> 00:16:29.609
I like to start
with an evil laugh.

147
00:16:33.131 --> 00:16:35.209
Hello, hairballs.

148
00:16:35.291 --> 00:16:38.170
You may have won today, Bolt,

149
00:16:38.251 --> 00:16:42.330
but in the end, we will
get your little Penny.

150
00:16:42.411 --> 00:16:45.850
Not likely, cat, for you've chosen
to follow the path of evil.

151
00:16:45.930 --> 00:16:50.169
Ultimately, it will destroy you, along
with your fiendish puppet master!

152
00:16:50.651 --> 00:16:53.490
- Wow!
- I know, right? Okay, watch this.

153
00:16:54.731 --> 00:16:57.050
She's a goner, dog.

154
00:16:57.132 --> 00:17:01.129
The Green-Eyed Man has a plan,
and soon, he will execute it.

155
00:17:02.411 --> 00:17:08.809
- Yeah, and then he will execute her.
- Nice.

156
00:17:08.891 --> 00:17:12.250
I would superbark you both back
into the hole you crawled out of,

157
00:17:12.331 --> 00:17:14.650
but I need you alive because
I've got a little message

158
00:17:14.771 --> 00:17:17.050
for you to take back to
your Green-Eyed Man.

159
00:17:17.131 --> 00:17:19.369
You tell him his old friend
Bolt said he better...

160
00:17:19.451 --> 00:17:20.729
Is it long?

161
00:17:21.650 --> 00:17:23.450
- Is what long?
- The message.

162
00:17:23.571 --> 00:17:26.970
Is it a long message? Because
I have a horrible memory.

163
00:17:27.091 --> 00:17:29.210
Yeah, I'll make it brief, all right?
You tell him I said I'm gonna...

164
00:17:29.331 --> 00:17:31.289
You know what? Why
don't we do this?

165
00:17:31.411 --> 00:17:33.530
You remember the first
half of the message,

166
00:17:33.651 --> 00:17:35.289
and then I'll
remember the second,

167
00:17:35.371 --> 00:17:37.370
and then we can pass it on to
the Green-Eyed Man together.

168
00:17:37.452 --> 00:17:40.170
Now, I don't care how the message
is translated, all right?

169
00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:41.609
Just do it, okay.

170
00:17:41.691 --> 00:17:43.930
Tell the Green-Eyed Man
that I will not sleep,

171
00:17:44.011 --> 00:17:47.690
I will not rest until my Penny
is safe from his evil clutches.

172
00:17:47.771 --> 00:17:48.890
You tell the Green-Eyed
Man that reckoning...

173
00:17:49.011 --> 00:17:50.249
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

174
00:17:50.331 --> 00:17:51.850
Way too many words.

175
00:17:51.930 --> 00:17:55.130
I was, like, "What?" And
then I was, like, "Huh?"

176
00:17:55.211 --> 00:17:59.290
And then, well, I got a little bored and...
Something about clutches?

177
00:17:59.371 --> 00:18:01.369
Anyway, I'll do my best. Ciao.

178
00:18:01.451 --> 00:18:04.730
By the way, huge fan. Love it, love you.
Gotta go. Thank you.

179
00:18:04.811 --> 00:18:09.770
Get back here, you sick,
revolting, loathsome little...

180
00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:15.530
Dogs.

181
00:18:16.811 --> 00:18:17.850
Cats.

182
00:18:25.291 --> 00:18:27.690
I'll never let them
get you, Penny.

183
00:18:45.650 --> 00:18:46.650
Are you ready, Bolt?

184
00:18:50.131 --> 00:18:55.290
Let's widen out camera three.
Ready four. Go four!

185
00:18:55.370 --> 00:18:57.289
And driver.

186
00:19:05.691 --> 00:19:07.130
Thanks, Larry.

187
00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:08.730
All right, Scooter.

188
00:19:08.811 --> 00:19:11.289
Find the grate. Ready
on the rubber bars.

189
00:19:15.371 --> 00:19:17.450
And track with them.

190
00:19:20.251 --> 00:19:22.170
The Calico supercomputer.

191
00:19:22.811 --> 00:19:27.130
If we can access it, we'll finally
learn where they're keeping my father.

192
00:19:45.171 --> 00:19:46.770
The weapon's hot.

193
00:19:48.211 --> 00:19:49.810
Heat vision time.

194
00:19:51.091 --> 00:19:52.651
Bolt, stare.

195
00:19:52.731 --> 00:19:53.850
Now!

196
00:20:06.651 --> 00:20:07.930
Nice move.

197
00:20:09.812 --> 00:20:11.410
Come on. Come on.

198
00:20:13.332 --> 00:20:18.571
Such devotion. It
brings tears to my eyes.

199
00:20:18.651 --> 00:20:19.930
Calico.

200
00:20:20.051 --> 00:20:26.010
Your father's discoveries could be
of great use to our organisation.

201
00:20:27.211 --> 00:20:32.971
I'm sure he'll be more accommodating
now that I've got his lucky Penny!

202
00:20:34.411 --> 00:20:35.450
Bolt!

203
00:20:37.211 --> 00:20:40.490
World domination is
within my grasp!

204
00:20:52.011 --> 00:20:54.970
How did your focus groups
feel about cliffhangers?

205
00:20:55.091 --> 00:20:57.850
You ask for unhappy
18-to-35-year-olds,

206
00:20:57.971 --> 00:21:02.811
I give you unhappy
18-to-35-year-olds.

207
00:21:02.931 --> 00:21:05.610
Bolt! It's okay, Bolt.
I'm fine.

208
00:21:05.691 --> 00:21:06.730
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

209
00:21:06.811 --> 00:21:08.091
Guards, stop her!

210
00:21:08.172 --> 00:21:10.411
- Hey, hey, hey, hey. Hold on.
- Bolt!

211
00:21:10.491 --> 00:21:13.050
Listen to him. He needs
to know I'm okay.

212
00:21:13.172 --> 00:21:15.130
Nope, you're not okay.

213
00:21:15.251 --> 00:21:18.091
You've been kidnapped by
the fiendish Dr Calico,

214
00:21:18.172 --> 00:21:20.090
at least that's what the
dog needs to think,

215
00:21:20.172 --> 00:21:22.571
but just imagine, close
your eyes and imagine

216
00:21:22.651 --> 00:21:26.490
how excited he'll be when he
saves you tomorrow. Okay?

217
00:21:26.611 --> 00:21:28.651
But he's gonna be
freaking out all night.

218
00:21:28.731 --> 00:21:30.490
- Please, just let me...
- What...

219
00:21:30.611 --> 00:21:32.731
Wait a second, what's
that behind your ear?

220
00:21:32.811 --> 00:21:34.131
Is that a...

221
00:21:34.412 --> 00:21:37.370
Yes, it is.
It's a pin. Let's do this.

222
00:21:37.532 --> 00:21:41.050
Let's take the pin and put it
in this conversation. Boop!

223
00:21:41.131 --> 00:21:42.731
And we will not take
it down, no, ma'am,

224
00:21:42.811 --> 00:21:44.411
until this matter is resolved.

225
00:21:44.532 --> 00:21:46.570
- But I just...
- Do you know what that reminds me of?

226
00:21:46.651 --> 00:21:49.850
The DVD release junket. Let's get going.
It's a big push.

227
00:21:49.971 --> 00:21:52.571
I want to go with a modern
look, something that says,

228
00:21:52.691 --> 00:21:54.650
"I'm 13, and I'm
fine with that."

229
00:21:54.771 --> 00:21:58.811
All right, okay. Let's give her some air.
Let's not crowd the talent.

230
00:22:07.451 --> 00:22:09.450
I've been working
on my evil laugh.

231
00:22:09.532 --> 00:22:10.837
'Cause everybody
has an evil laugh.

232
00:22:12.411 --> 00:22:13.371
Like that.

233
00:22:13.492 --> 00:22:15.610
Okay, here's the thing. You're
not ready for the evil laugh.

234
00:22:15.731 --> 00:22:18.251
You could do a chuckle, like
a mildly upset chuckle,

235
00:22:18.331 --> 00:22:19.771
after my evil laugh.

236
00:22:19.851 --> 00:22:20.810
Listen to mine.

237
00:22:22.011 --> 00:22:23.051
Hey, Bolt.

238
00:22:23.772 --> 00:22:25.011
Big fan!

239
00:22:26.171 --> 00:22:27.731
Bolt! Come back!

240
00:22:31.451 --> 00:22:32.651
I'm too late.

241
00:22:32.732 --> 00:22:35.571
- Bolt! Help!
- I'm coming, Penny!

242
00:22:36.731 --> 00:22:38.011
Bolt! Help!

243
00:22:40.571 --> 00:22:42.490
Hold on, Penny! Hold on!

244
00:22:43.412 --> 00:22:47.450
Bolt! Help! Bolt! Help!

245
00:22:58.012 --> 00:22:59.210
Penny!

246
00:23:11.932 --> 00:23:14.171
Bolt! Here, Bolt!

247
00:23:38.172 --> 00:23:39.291
Huh?

